{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-js","path":"/2020/first-automated-room","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>When I started out on automating my house I was checking various technologies to base this system on,\nin the end I settled upon Zigbee which is a mesh network, so when device item can't directly communicate with the\ndriver it will run it along another device.<br>\nSo this means that every powered device is also a repeater of the signals.</p>\n<p>So the bathroom is now the first room that has been automated,\nthe fan that removes the moist from the air now starts when it value goes above a threshold,\nwhen it goes below it will switch off.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 542px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/dd5d09d767a1fbeb0d330586bca5c2a5/c0388/bathroom.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 47.852760736196316%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/dd5d09d767a1fbeb0d330586bca5c2a5/94563/bathroom.webp 163w,\n/static/dd5d09d767a1fbeb0d330586bca5c2a5/647a8/bathroom.webp 325w,\n/static/dd5d09d767a1fbeb0d330586bca5c2a5/3f954/bathroom.webp 542w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 542px) 100vw, 542px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/dd5d09d767a1fbeb0d330586bca5c2a5/222b7/bathroom.png 163w,\n/static/dd5d09d767a1fbeb0d330586bca5c2a5/ff46a/bathroom.png 325w,\n/static/dd5d09d767a1fbeb0d330586bca5c2a5/c0388/bathroom.png 542w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 542px) 100vw, 542px\"\n          type=\"image/png\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/dd5d09d767a1fbeb0d330586bca5c2a5/c0388/bathroom.png\"\n          alt=\"Bathroom view\"\n          title=\"Bathroom view\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n          style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>This is actually rather funny to start showering and then all of a sudden the fan will start running.</p>\n<p>Still one temporary downside is that when the fan is running (which also repeater) is that the repeated signal almost stops\nbut this will be resolved when adding more devices to the network.</p>\n<h3>Next step</h3>\n<p>The next step will be the living room for the lighting. Might add an automation rule to turn off the lights when\nwatching a movie, and turning it back on when the movie is paused or stopped. </p>\n<p>Will post an update when the rest of the hardware arrives!</p>","fields":{"date":"May 13, 2020","path":"/2020/first-automated-room"},"frontmatter":{"title":"First automated room","description":"Babysteps to a smart home","topics":["smart home"]}},"allMarkdownRemark":{"nodes":[{"id":"06ceccec-c1c2-5dd1-a2a0-6d82d527ccf0","fields":{"date":"July 31, 2020","path":"/2020/second-automation"},"frontmatter":{"title":"My second automation"}},{"id":"d556e09b-50ee-55ed-bb12-d8ff3b4cf2f0","fields":{"date":"June 01, 2020","path":"/2020/change-of-automation-plans"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Change of plans"}}]}},"pageContext":{"id":"956d403f-0925-5101-b3c8-57539e0e8167","topics":["smart home"]}}}